Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 9/14/98

The MPEG-2 video decoder is working now.  It can successfully decode the
three bitstreams from EchoStar.  Currently it can only decode MP@ML
frame pictures because it is the most widely used bitstream parameters.
It can be expanded to accept other profiles or field pictures in the
future when it is needed.

I have started working on the video encoder.  Some preliminary I-frame
only bitstreams have been generated.  Will work on encoding P and B-frame
this week.

Exchanged some emails with the Patent attroney on the DPI patent draft.
